# Filesystem Rules

Purpose:
Constrain file operations to a predictable and reviewable subset of the repository.

Rules:
- Operate only inside the project workspace.
- Do not create new top-level directories unless the task clearly requires them.
- Prefer existing project structure over introducing new structural patterns.
- Place new files in the most specific existing directory that matches their purpose.
- Do not duplicate existing modules under slightly different names.
- Do not create temporary files that remain in the repository after task completion.
- Do not store generated runtime artifacts in source directories.
- Keep test fixtures under tests/fixtures/.
- Keep documentation under docs/ unless it belongs in README.md.
- Keep automation or helper scripts under scripts/.
- Keep knowledge-base test files under tests/fixtures/knowledge/.
- Do not introduce hidden state files unless the task explicitly requires them.
- If a file must be moved or renamed, update all affected imports and references in the same change.

Expected behavior:
- Respect the intended layout of the repository.
- Avoid structural drift.
- Keep all added files discoverable and logically placed.